They'd only just met on vacation.

1044
01:05:40,851 --> 01:05:43,650
They didn't even speak
the same language.

1045
01:05:43,650 --> 01:05:47,249
Yet they were inseparable.

1046
01:05:48,409 --> 01:05:51,368
There was such a bond
between them.

1047
01:05:52,008 --> 01:05:53,968
A strong bond.

1048
01:05:53,968 --> 01:05:56,687
And she came every day.

1049
01:05:56,687 --> 01:05:58,487
Every day.

1050
01:06:03,086 --> 01:06:05,885
She'd hold your hand.

1051
01:06:05,885 --> 01:06:07,245
She had made up her mind

1052
01:06:07,245 --> 01:06:09,484
that she wasn't going
to leave your side.

1053
01:06:09,484 --> 01:06:11,764
And she didn't.

1054
01:06:17,242 --> 01:06:19,642
Why are you telling me this now?

1055
01:06:19,642 --> 01:06:21,402
Why only now?

1056
01:06:21,402 --> 01:06:22,681
I've been here.

1057
01:06:22,681 --> 01:06:26,360
I haven't hidden anything from you.

1058
01:06:26,360 --> 01:06:29,279
I've been right here in front of you
the whole time.

1059
01:06:29,279 --> 01:06:32,639
All you had to do
was open your eyes.

1060
01:06:33,239 --> 01:06:37,838
It was you who questioned me
when I came out of the coma.

1061
01:06:41,237 --> 01:06:45,596
You were the only one
who believed me.

1062
01:06:46,396 --> 01:06:48,835
Yes.

1063
01:07:09,510 --> 01:07:12,910
Kay, where are you?

1064
01:07:15,509 --> 01:07:17,269
Nathan, it's Rachel.

1065
01:07:17,269 --> 01:07:18,789
Everybody here is looking for you.

1066
01:07:18,789 --> 01:07:19,988
Where are you?

1067
01:07:19,988 --> 01:07:21,908
I left six messages
on your cell phone.

1068
01:07:21,908 --> 01:07:24,987
- Will you call me?
- Kay?

1069
01:07:26,347 --> 01:07:28,266
Where are you?
What's wrong with me?

1070
01:07:28,266 --> 01:07:29,986
First of all, don't panic.

1071
01:07:29,986 --> 01:07:33,105
There's a clinic
at the northeast corner

1072
01:07:33,105 --> 01:07:35,064
of 44th and Lexington.

1073
01:07:35,064 --> 01:07:37,065
They'll give you a shot of glucagon.

1074
01:07:37,065 --> 01:07:39,184
- Lexington and what?
- 44th.

1075
01:08:11,576 --> 01:08:13,496
It's okay, Nathan.

1076
01:08:13,496 --> 01:08:16,175
I'm here.

1077
01:08:34,451 --> 01:08:38,091
You're asking me
where we go after we die?

1078
01:08:38,091 --> 01:08:41,010
Nathan, knowing whether
there is an afterlife

1079
01:08:41,010 --> 01:08:42,889
is not the point.

1080
01:08:42,889 --> 01:08:47,089
The important thing is
being alive before you die.

1081
01:08:47,129 --> 01:08:50,687
Today, now.
Fully alive.

1082
01:08:50,847 --> 01:08:53,767
The wonder of life
is in the here and now.

1083
01:08:53,767 --> 01:08:57,246
We always find out too late.

1084
01:09:02,165 --> 01:09:04,204
I've got to go get my daughter,

1085
01:09:04,244 --> 01:09:05,965
and I'm frightened for her.

1086
01:09:05,965 --> 01:09:09,404
So you're going to come with me.

1087
01:09:09,404 --> 01:09:11,323
You're going to come with us.

1088
01:09:11,323 --> 01:09:14,202
This white light, you haven't seen it
on yourself yet, right?

1089
01:09:14,202 --> 01:09:15,562
- No.
- Good.

1090
01:09:15,562 --> 01:09:17,162
That means if you're
on the plane with us

1091
01:09:17,162 --> 01:09:19,001
nothing will happen.

1092
01:09:19,001 --> 01:09:21,201
I don't want to put Tracey in danger.

1093
01:10:14,228 --> 01:10:16,388
Is it him or her?

1094
01:10:41,343 --> 01:10:44,222
This light, what's it like exactly?

1095
01:10:44,222 --> 01:10:45,702
I told you.

1096
01:10:45,702 --> 01:10:48,301
It's like a white halo
shining from the person.

1097
01:10:48,301 --> 01:10:50,060
And you see it all the time?

1098
01:10:50,060 --> 01:10:53,180
No, you only see it once,
and then...

1099
01:10:53,180 --> 01:10:54,459
but that's not what's important.

1100
01:10:54,459 --> 01:10:56,779
I know, I know.

1101
01:11:24,591 --> 01:11:26,791
So who is he anyway?

1102
01:11:26,791 --> 01:11:29,270
- A doctor.
- You work together?

1103
01:11:29,270 --> 01:11:32,070
Not really.
It's kinda complicated.

1104
01:11:32,150 --> 01:11:34,431
He's a friend of yours?

1105
01:11:36,550 --> 01:11:38,910
Why is he here?

1106
01:11:39,350 --> 01:11:40,870
Just traveling with me.

1107
01:11:40,870 --> 01:11:44,229
- I didn't want to travel alone.
- Like Tracey.

1108
01:11:44,229 --> 01:11:46,829
Yeah.
Like Tracey, yeah.

1109
01:11:51,189 --> 01:11:53,229
It's happening tonight?

1110
01:11:53,229 --> 01:11:55,389
Maybe.

1111
01:11:55,389 --> 01:11:56,869
I hope so.

1112
01:11:56,869 --> 01:11:59,789
You can never know in advance.

1113
01:12:48,426 --> 01:12:51,705
You know why I came?
The real reason.

1114
01:12:52,505 --> 01:12:56,225
You came because
you promised her you would.

1115
01:12:56,664 --> 01:12:59,824
You came because
you love your daughter.

1116
01:13:00,984 --> 01:13:03,144
- Don't you?
- Of course I do.

1117
01:13:03,144 --> 01:13:05,464
But there's
something else.

1118
01:13:06,183 --> 01:13:07,864
Naturally.

1119
01:13:07,864 --> 01:13:10,423
Look, Nathan,

1120
01:13:10,423 --> 01:13:12,103
I have a life here

1121
01:13:12,103 --> 01:13:14,383
and I'm trying to build
something solid with Tracey...

1122
01:13:15,903 --> 01:13:18,023
Wait, listen!

1123
01:13:20,423 --> 01:13:23,862
I think I know what
you're trying to tell me

1124
01:13:23,862 --> 01:13:28,342
and I think that we can
avoid this sort of...

1125
01:13:29,742 --> 01:13:31,062
Unpleasantness?

1126
01:13:31,062 --> 01:13:34,662
You know exactly what I mean.

1127
01:13:39,222 --> 01:13:40,862
I want you to come with me.

1128
01:13:40,862 --> 01:13:43,542
I want the three of us
to go back to New York.

1129
01:13:43,542 --> 01:13:45,941
I want you to come home.

1130
01:13:49,180 --> 01:13:52,260
Avoid just that sort of thing.

1131
01:14:53,096 --> 01:14:56,096
Tracey, don't look.

1132
01:15:57,732 --> 01:15:59,492
You go back alone.
I'm staying here.

1133
01:15:59,492 --> 01:16:01,132
I want to stay here.

1134
01:16:01,132 --> 01:16:04,931
- With Tracey?
- Yes, with Tracey, yes.

1135
01:16:05,611 --> 01:16:07,491
- You still need me.
- No.

1136
01:16:07,491 --> 01:16:09,251
I don't know.

1137
01:16:09,251 --> 01:16:11,651
I'm staying, that's all.

1138
01:16:13,570 --> 01:16:18,010
Is there something I should know?

1139
01:16:18,250 --> 01:16:20,810
Something you haven't told me?

1140
01:16:24,770 --> 01:16:27,530
I'm going to miss my plane.

1141
01:16:44,289 --> 01:16:46,849
Honey, do you know how to use it?

1142
01:16:46,849 --> 01:16:49,808
Huh? Press here.
Yes, that's it.

1143
01:16:49,808 --> 01:16:52,248
Good.

1144
01:16:53,568 --> 01:16:55,247
- Daddy?
- Yes.

1145
01:16:55,247 --> 01:16:58,568
The people we saw a while ago...

1146
01:16:58,688 --> 01:17:00,727
- Yes?
- The ones in the accident.

1147
01:17:00,767 --> 01:17:03,247
- Yes?
- The ones who died.

1148
01:17:03,647 --> 01:17:07,807
- Yes.
- Will they have crosses too?

1149
01:17:07,807 --> 01:17:09,727
I don't know.
Maybe.

1150
01:17:11,766 --> 01:17:14,886
But they're not buried
under them, right?

1151
01:17:14,886 --> 01:17:16,006
Who?

1152
01:17:16,006 --> 01:17:18,046
Oh, no.

1153
01:17:19,526 --> 01:17:22,806
But Paul, he's buried
under one, right?

1154
01:17:23,166 --> 01:17:24,366
Yes, honey.

1155
01:17:24,366 --> 01:17:25,686
Listen, honey,

1156
01:17:25,726 --> 01:17:28,245
if anything ever happens to me,

1157
01:17:28,285 --> 01:17:30,285
if I get to feel sick or,
I don't know...

1158
01:17:30,285 --> 01:17:31,605
what do you do?

1159
01:17:31,605 --> 01:17:33,125
- I call Mommy.
- You call Mommy.

1160
01:17:33,125 --> 01:17:34,165
Good, right.

1161
01:17:34,204 --> 01:17:36,565
And who else,
if Mommy isn't there?

1162
01:17:36,565 --> 01:17:38,764
If you have to call for help,
what do you do?

1163
01:17:38,764 --> 01:17:40,685
- I scream.
- You scream?

1164
01:17:40,685 --> 01:17:42,764
Honey, I'm serious.
What do you do?

1165
01:17:42,764 --> 01:17:47,124
I cry?
I know, relax.

1166
01:17:47,124 --> 01:17:48,364
I press here.

1167
01:17:48,364 --> 01:17:50,563
You already showed me.

1168
01:17:51,484 --> 01:17:53,243
Okay.

1169
01:18:31,041 --> 01:18:33,961
Honey,
you remember when...

1170
01:18:33,961 --> 01:18:36,240
when Paul died?

1171
01:18:36,240 --> 01:18:38,401
Do you remember?

1172
01:18:39,280 --> 01:18:42,280
Well, when he died...

1173
01:18:43,200 --> 01:18:44,920
I found a garden slug.

1174
01:18:44,920 --> 01:18:46,959
I remember.

1175
01:18:47,520 --> 01:18:49,999
I remember you asked
a lot of questions.

1176
01:18:49,999 --> 01:18:52,160
Lots and lots of questions.

1177
01:18:52,160 --> 01:18:54,840
Like what?

1178
01:18:54,840 --> 01:18:57,639
You asked us where he was.

1179
01:18:57,639 --> 01:18:59,559
We told you,
"Paul is in heaven.

1180
01:18:59,559 --> 01:19:01,519
In heaven with the angels".

1181
01:19:01,519 --> 01:19:04,758
And you asked us
if you could go see him.

1182
01:19:04,758 --> 01:19:07,278
You wanted to go see him.

1183
01:19:07,278 --> 01:19:11,159
And I don't know
if we always said the right thing.

1184
01:19:11,518 --> 01:19:14,718
- It isn't true?
- What isn't true?

1185
01:19:14,718 --> 01:19:16,398
That Paul's in heaven?

1186
01:19:16,398 --> 01:19:17,918
He could be.

1187
01:19:17,918 --> 01:19:19,198
Maybe.

1188
01:19:19,198 --> 01:19:20,717
But to tell you the truth,

1189
01:19:20,717 --> 01:19:22,077
nobody really knows.
Nobody can know.

1190
01:19:22,077 --> 01:19:23,957
- It's something that...
- I know.

1191
01:19:23,957 --> 01:19:25,837
You do?

1192
01:19:25,837 --> 01:19:28,876
When we die they put us
into the ground...

1193
01:19:28,876 --> 01:19:32,397
and slugs eat us, of course,

1194
01:19:32,397 --> 01:19:34,636
and then we disappear.

1195
01:19:34,636 --> 01:19:36,437
And then we don't exist any more.

1196
01:19:36,437 --> 01:19:39,876
Nobody can be sure of that either.

1197
01:19:40,076 --> 01:19:41,916
But you know,
I believe one thing.

1198
01:19:41,916 --> 01:19:44,476
- Want me to tell you?
- Mm-hmm.

1199
01:19:44,476 --> 01:19:46,836
I think just because we die

1200
01:19:46,836 --> 01:19:50,156
doesn't mean we don't exist anymore.

1201
01:19:50,156 --> 01:19:52,475
Maybe we exist someplace else.

1202
01:19:52,715 --> 01:19:54,635
And you know why I think that?

1203
01:19:56,875 --> 01:19:59,435
When you see a boat vanish...

1204
01:19:59,435 --> 01:20:02,315
have you ever seen a boat
vanish on the horizon?

1205
01:20:02,874 --> 01:20:05,474
When a boat disappears
in the distance,

1206
01:20:05,474 --> 01:20:07,114
it vanishes,

1207
01:20:07,114 --> 01:20:09,634
but does that mean
it doesn't exist anymore?

1208
01:20:09,634 --> 01:20:11,514
No.

1209
01:20:11,514 --> 01:20:13,193
Right.

1210
01:20:13,193 --> 01:20:14,953
I believe dying is like that.

1211
01:20:14,953 --> 01:20:17,993
It's like a boat
vanishing on the horizon.

1212
01:20:17,993 --> 01:20:23,193
Just because you can't see it,
doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

1213
01:23:25,980 --> 01:23:28,980
- Can we talk?
- Why did you come back?

1214
01:23:30,860 --> 01:23:32,619
We didn't want to fly.

1215
01:23:32,619 --> 01:23:35,220
Tracey and I were too scared
to take the plane.

1216
01:23:35,220 --> 01:23:38,259
Besides, I'm in no hurry
to get home.

1217
01:23:38,339 --> 01:23:39,699
So what do you plan to do?

1218
01:23:39,699 --> 01:23:41,779
Here?
I don't know.

1219
01:23:41,779 --> 01:23:42,739
Hang out.

1220
01:23:42,739 --> 01:23:44,738
Spend some time with Tracey.

1221
01:23:44,738 --> 01:23:46,098
Go for walks.

1222
01:23:46,098 --> 01:23:48,818
You could maybe point out
some places to go.

1223
01:23:48,818 --> 01:23:51,938
- Tracey told me you two...
- Places to go?

1224
01:23:52,458 --> 01:23:54,338
Nathan, what's the matter with you?

1225
01:23:54,338 --> 01:23:56,977
- Nothing.
- What do you mean, nothing?

1226
01:23:56,977 --> 01:23:59,538
You call me in the middle
of the night as if...

1227
01:23:59,538 --> 01:24:01,658
I don't know.

1228
01:24:02,537 --> 01:24:04,977
Then you show up two days early
with this strange guy,

1229
01:24:04,977 --> 01:24:06,058
and you come out
with these remarks.

1230
01:24:06,058 --> 01:24:09,137
Now you're talking
about going for walks?

1231
01:24:09,137 --> 01:24:10,657
What's going on?

1232
01:24:10,657 --> 01:24:12,817
You have troubles
at the firm, is that it?

1233
01:24:12,817 --> 01:24:14,217
No, not really.

1234
01:24:14,217 --> 01:24:16,657
Then what?
Are you sick?

1235
01:24:16,657 --> 01:24:20,176
No, not that I'm aware of.

1236
01:24:20,736 --> 01:24:22,056
Not that you're aware of?

1237
01:24:22,056 --> 01:24:23,416
No.

1238
01:24:23,416 --> 01:24:26,096
Just a little hypoglycemia.

1239
01:24:44,815 --> 01:24:46,615
When does it happen?

1240
01:24:49,774 --> 01:24:52,974
Two hours from now,
maybe sooner.

1241
01:25:00,613 --> 01:25:03,253
We had ice cream last night,

1242
01:25:03,253 --> 01:25:05,813
and we talked about Paul.

1243
01:25:05,933 --> 01:25:07,653
On the road
we saw some crosses,

1244
01:25:07,653 --> 01:25:10,573
and afterwards she wanted to...

1245
01:25:11,973 --> 01:25:14,773
does she talk to you about it?

1246
01:25:15,052 --> 01:25:16,732
Not so much these days.

1247
01:25:16,732 --> 01:25:17,972
But is she all right?

1248
01:25:17,972 --> 01:25:19,652
The last time on the phone
when I called,

1249
01:25:19,652 --> 01:25:23,532
- she was already asleep...
- She wasn't asleep.

1250
01:25:24,292 --> 01:25:26,291
She wasn't asleep?

1251
01:25:26,291 --> 01:25:28,132
- No.
- Can't you take a break?

1252
01:25:28,132 --> 01:25:29,412
Five minutes.

1253
01:25:29,412 --> 01:25:32,211
Nathan, in one hour
this flower will be dead.

1254
01:25:32,211 --> 01:25:34,171
It blooms one night a year,
just the once,

1255
01:25:34,171 --> 01:25:37,531
- and I still have...
- Yes, I know that, but...

1256
01:25:39,171 --> 01:25:41,170
sorry.

1257
01:25:50,370 --> 01:25:53,210
When we went home
to New York...

1258
01:25:53,810 --> 01:25:55,969
do you remember
the first thing you did?

1259
01:25:55,969 --> 01:25:58,969
The first.

1260
01:26:00,009 --> 01:26:02,769
You called the office.

1261
01:26:03,329 --> 01:26:06,448
You wanted to know
if anyone had called.

1262
01:26:07,608 --> 01:26:09,929
We'd just buried Paul,

1263
01:26:09,929 --> 01:26:13,128
and you disappeared
into your work.

1264
01:26:15,288 --> 01:26:17,568
You shut yourself off
in your anger.

1265
01:26:17,568 --> 01:26:20,888
But Tracey and I were still there.

1266
01:26:20,888 --> 01:26:23,408
We were alive.

1267
01:26:23,927 --> 01:26:25,647
I know you felt guilty.

1268
01:26:25,647 --> 01:26:27,688
I know that you blamed yourself

1269
01:26:27,688 --> 01:26:28,888
because you heard him cry

1270
01:26:28,888 --> 01:26:30,047
and you didn't go check on him.

1271
01:26:30,047 --> 01:26:32,927
- He called me.
- No.

1272
01:26:32,927 --> 01:26:36,407
Paul cried
and he went back to sleep,

1273
01:26:36,407 --> 01:26:38,247
and even if...

1274
01:26:38,247 --> 01:26:41,966
He called me,
but I didn't go to him.

1275
01:26:41,966 --> 01:26:45,486
Nathan, Paul didn't call anyone.

1276
01:26:45,766 --> 01:26:47,166
Paul's dead.

1277
01:26:47,166 --> 01:26:50,526
I've accepted that and so has Tracey.

1278
01:26:50,526 --> 01:26:53,405
She's accepted it
in her own little way.

1279
01:26:53,805 --> 01:26:55,806
And now you... you need
to accept it too.

1280
01:26:55,806 --> 01:26:58,805
- I'm ready.
- You need to stop...

1281
01:26:59,645 --> 01:27:02,085
I don't know.

1282
01:27:02,924 --> 01:27:04,284
I don't know, Nathan.

1283
01:27:04,284 --> 01:27:06,845
I don't know what to tell you.

1284
01:27:07,324 --> 01:27:12,724
I'm ready.
I came back to tell you.

1285
01:27:13,724 --> 01:27:16,523
And if anything
ever happens to me...

1286
01:27:17,324 --> 01:27:20,164
Why do you say that?

1287
01:27:20,164 --> 01:27:23,283
I wanted you to know
that I've changed.

1288
01:27:42,482 --> 01:27:45,322
I know a river not far from here.

1289
01:27:48,002 --> 01:27:50,561
If you want, I could
show you how to get there.

1290
01:27:50,561 --> 01:27:51,801
Yeah.

1291
01:27:51,801 --> 01:27:54,081
I'd like that.

1292
01:27:54,361 --> 01:27:57,041
A pretty river.

1293
01:27:58,120 --> 01:28:00,521
Right.

1294
01:28:05,240 --> 01:28:09,440
- Not very far?
- No.

1295
01:28:22,200 --> 01:28:25,679
Forgive me.

1296
01:28:53,917 --> 01:28:56,917
Hi, this is Rachel calling
from Nathan's office.

1297
01:28:56,917 --> 01:28:58,956
I'm sorry to bother you, but...

1298
01:28:58,956 --> 01:29:02,517
he's not at home and hasn't been by
the office in several days.

1299
01:29:02,517 --> 01:29:04,756
We can't reach him
on his cell phone either.

1300
01:29:04,756 --> 01:29:07,836
We're worried and thought
maybe you'd heard from him.

1301
01:29:07,836 --> 01:29:10,396
Could you please call us
if you've got any news?

1302
01:29:39,994 --> 01:29:42,554
They're looking for you.

1303
01:29:44,194 --> 01:29:47,114
Yes, I know.

1304
01:30:07,912 --> 01:30:09,632
"Someone once told me,

1305
01:30:09,632 --> 01:30:13,872
"'The wonder of life is
in the here and now. '

1306
01:30:14,471 --> 01:30:17,191
"I'm going to die soon.

1307
01:30:17,671 --> 01:30:22,071
"And yet, I'm no longer
dominated by fear.

1308
01:30:24,791 --> 01:30:27,710
"Life is full of riches...

1309
01:30:27,710 --> 01:30:29,670
"the gestures, the laughter,

1310
01:30:29,670 --> 01:30:32,430
"the joy we shared.

1311
01:30:32,870 --> 01:30:35,630
"I remember it all.

1312
01:30:40,229 --> 01:30:42,430
"I remember your breathing too,

1313
01:30:42,430 --> 01:30:43,789
"when you slept in the car.

1314
01:30:43,789 --> 01:30:46,629
"Mommy's face when she saw us.

1315
01:30:46,629 --> 01:30:48,869
"We did a lot of things together.

1316
01:30:48,869 --> 01:30:50,668
Lots and lots of things".

1317
01:30:53,308 --> 01:30:55,869
"I've learned a lot.

1318
01:30:56,228 --> 01:30:59,508
I've met some wonderful people".

1319
01:30:59,748 --> 01:31:03,148
Hi, I... I'm Jennifer.

1320
01:31:14,907 --> 01:31:17,107
"Cherish your happiness.

1321
01:31:17,107 --> 01:31:20,426
"Savor it at every instant.

1322
01:31:22,227 --> 01:31:23,546
"And above all,

1323
01:31:23,546 --> 01:31:27,066
"don't get upset if you think of me.

1324
01:31:27,426 --> 01:31:29,106
"Don't be sad.

1325
01:31:47,545 --> 01:31:50,224
"And one day,
if you want to talk to me...

1326
01:31:50,224 --> 01:31:52,624
"if you really want to...

1327
01:31:52,624 --> 01:31:54,344
"pick a spot you like.

1328
01:31:54,344 --> 01:31:58,024
"A spot where we used
to go together.

1329
01:32:00,384 --> 01:32:03,783
"You'll be able
to talk to me... you'll see.

1330
01:32:04,464 --> 01:32:07,104
"Because I'll be there.

1331
01:32:16,023 --> 01:32:17,463
"And remember,

1332
01:32:17,463 --> 01:32:21,102
"don't be ashamed to tell people
you care about

1333
01:32:21,102 --> 01:32:23,423
"that you love them.

1334
01:32:24,222 --> 01:32:28,342
I love you both very much".

1335
01:32:49,980 --> 01:32:52,060
Did you sleep well?

1336
01:32:52,060 --> 01:32:53,940
Yes.

1337
01:32:55,100 --> 01:32:57,459
Want me to make you a fresh pot?

1338
01:32:57,459 --> 01:32:59,820
No, it's okay.

1339
01:34:09,775 --> 01:34:11,854
I need to see you.
You've got to get out here.

1340
01:34:11,854 --> 01:34:13,655
I need to see you now,
understand?

1341
01:34:13,655 --> 01:34:15,694
- I'm here.
- Take the first flight...

1342
01:34:15,694 --> 01:34:17,694
I'm here.
I'm here with you.

1343
01:34:17,694 --> 01:34:19,373
What do you mean here?

1344
01:34:19,373 --> 01:34:22,293
On the road to the airport...
the Crossroads Motel.

1345
01:34:22,293 --> 01:34:23,934
I'm here.

1346
01:34:23,934 --> 01:34:26,773
I'll wait for you here.

1347
01:35:06,451 --> 01:35:08,170
You lied to me from the start.

1348
01:35:08,170 --> 01:35:09,490
No.

1349
01:35:09,490 --> 01:35:11,050
You said it was me.

1350
01:35:11,050 --> 01:35:13,010
You said so.

1351
01:35:13,410 --> 01:35:16,010
You said I was the one
who was going to die.

1352
01:35:16,010 --> 01:35:19,090
So what did I see?
Tell me.

1353
01:35:19,090 --> 01:35:21,290
I was the one who
was supposed to die.

1354
01:35:21,290 --> 01:35:22,889
It was supposed to be me!

1355
01:35:22,889 --> 01:35:24,769
You said so!

1356
01:35:24,769 --> 01:35:27,689
No.

1357
01:35:30,129 --> 01:35:32,849
Nathan?

1358
01:35:39,608 --> 01:35:41,008
Tracey, have you seen daddy?

1359
01:35:41,008 --> 01:35:42,968
No.

1360
01:36:05,287 --> 01:36:07,646
I'm a Messenger, right?

1361
01:36:08,846 --> 01:36:11,046
Yes.

1362
01:36:11,406 --> 01:36:14,286
And my wife is going to die.

1363
01:36:16,126 --> 01:36:17,926
Yes.

1364
01:36:17,926 --> 01:36:19,206
Why didn't you tell me

1365
01:36:19,206 --> 01:36:21,405
when you came to see me
the first time

1366
01:36:21,405 --> 01:36:23,445
instead of being so mysterious.

1367
01:36:23,445 --> 01:36:25,845
The swan's song and all that bullshit.

1368
01:36:25,845 --> 01:36:27,285
You wouldn't have believed me.

1369
01:36:27,285 --> 01:36:28,764
You never would have believed me.

1370
01:36:28,764 --> 01:36:30,605
I was trying to prepare you.

1371
01:36:30,605 --> 01:36:32,245
Prepare me for what?

1372
01:36:32,245 --> 01:36:34,364
You're a Messenger.

1373
01:36:34,364 --> 01:36:35,924
A teacher of life.

1374
01:36:35,924 --> 01:36:37,724
But to be a teacher of life

1375
01:36:37,724 --> 01:36:40,364
you have to remember
your own mortality.

1376
01:36:40,364 --> 01:36:43,284
- You have to.
- But why does she have to die?

1377
01:36:43,284 --> 01:36:45,003
Why her?

1378
01:36:45,003 --> 01:36:49,283
All Messengers lose
the person closest to them.

1379
01:36:50,323 --> 01:36:53,883
That's the price...
the price of grace.

1380
01:36:54,123 --> 01:36:55,523
I paid the same price.

1381
01:36:55,523 --> 01:36:56,963
But in time,

1382
01:36:56,963 --> 01:36:59,643
you'll know that you
were there until the very end.

1383
01:36:59,643 --> 01:37:02,442
Through the very end.

1384
01:37:02,962 --> 01:37:05,003
That's the price
of becoming a Messenger.

1385
01:37:05,003 --> 01:37:06,842
But I never asked for this.

1386
01:37:06,842 --> 01:37:09,522
Nobody ever gave me a choice.

1387
01:37:10,242 --> 01:37:11,921
You made your choice, Nathan.

1388
01:37:11,921 --> 01:37:14,402
You made your choice
when you decided to come back

1389
01:37:14,402 --> 01:37:16,521
after you had died on that road.

1390
01:37:16,521 --> 01:37:17,961
And you came back.

1391
01:37:17,961 --> 01:37:19,722
And now you know why.

1392
01:37:19,722 --> 01:37:22,361
What brought you back?

1393
01:37:23,521 --> 01:37:25,081
A face.

1394
01:37:25,081 --> 01:37:26,960
Whose face?

1395
01:37:28,480 --> 01:37:30,920
Claire's face.

1396
01:37:32,920 --> 01:37:35,360
She was afraid.

1397
01:37:36,960 --> 01:37:39,520
She needed me.

1398
01:38:29,476 --> 01:38:31,636
Where were you?

1399
01:38:33,556 --> 01:38:35,996
I got lost.

1400
01:38:37,876 --> 01:38:40,156
We were waiting for you.

1401
01:38:40,236 --> 01:38:42,715
I got lost.

1402
01:38:45,435 --> 01:38:48,275
We thought that you'd left us...

1403
01:38:49,435 --> 01:38:52,595
that you'd...

1404
01:38:55,275 --> 01:38:59,034
- We were worried.
- I know.

1405
01:38:59,674 --> 01:39:02,034
But don't be scared.

1406
01:39:02,034 --> 01:39:04,554
I'm here now.

1407
01:39:05,354 --> 01:39:08,273
I'll never leave you again.

